<p>If you open that directory, you can see where the <code>bootstrap.css</code> file
lives. Notice, it's <em>not</em> a Sass file - just regular old CSS. There actually
<em>is</em> a Sass version of Bootstrap, and you can totally use this instead
if you want to control your Bootstrap variables.</p>
<p>But the question is, can we push plain CSS files through our Sass-processing
<code>addStyle</code> function? Sure! Let's add <code>config.bowerDir</code> then <code>/bootstrap/dist/css/bootstrap.css</code>:</p>
